08/11/2006
BELGRADE, Serbia -- The country's 240-member parliament proclaimed the new Serbian Constitution on Wednesday (November 8th), replacing the outdated Milosevic-era one. The new constitution, which defines Kosovo as an integral part of Serbia, was initially passed by deputies on September 30th and confirmed in a nationwide referendum on October 28th-29th. (Beta, B92 - 08/11/06)
